---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ZodiacSignFinder from '../components/ZodiacSignFinder.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Zodiac Sign Finder — What's Your Star Sign? | Clockr"
	description="Find your Western zodiac sign, element, ruling planet, key traits, and birthstone instantly from your birth date."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="zsf-page">
		<div class="zsf-header">
			<div class="zsf-eyebrow">
				<span class="zsf-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="zsf-title">
				<span class="zsf-gradient">Zodiac Sign Finder</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="zsf-subtitle">
				Find your star sign and birthstone instantly
			</p>
		</div>

		<ZodiacSignFinder client:load />

		<section class="zsf-how">
			<h2 class="zsf-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="zsf-how-card">
				<p>
					Western (tropical) zodiac signs divide the year into twelve segments
					based on the sun&apos;s apparent path through the sky. Each sign
					corresponds to a date range on the calendar — for example, Cancer runs
					from roughly 21 June to 22 July. Enter your birth date and Clockr
					matches it to the sign whose range includes that day, using the
					traditional date boundaries used in most horoscope charts.
				</p>
				<p>
					Astrology is a cultural tradition enjoyed by millions worldwide, but
					it is not supported by scientific evidence. Zodiac signs, elements,
					and planetary rulerships are symbolic rather than factual — think of
					this tool as a fun way to explore a familiar system, not a guide to
					your personality or future.
				</p>
				<p>
					If you were born within a day or two of a sign boundary, you may hear
					people call you a &ldquo;cusp&rdquo; birth — born close to where one
					sign ends and the next begins. Exact cusp dates can shift slightly
					from year to year because the sun&apos;s position at a given calendar
					date varies by a day or so. Clockr uses the standard fixed date ranges;
					for precise astronomical positions, a professional ephemeris would be
					needed.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="zsf-faq">
			<h2 class="zsf-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="zsf-faq-list">
				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>What is my zodiac sign based on my birth date?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Your zodiac sign is determined by where the sun appeared to sit in
							the sky on the day you were born. Each of the twelve signs covers
							a specific range of calendar dates — Aries from late March to
							mid-April, Taurus from mid-April to mid-May, and so on. Enter your
							birth date above and Clockr instantly shows which sign&apos;s range
							includes your birthday.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>What are the dates for each zodiac sign?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The twelve signs and their typical date ranges are: Capricorn (22
							Dec – 19 Jan), Aquarius (20 Jan – 18 Feb), Pisces (19 Feb – 20
							Mar), Aries (21 Mar – 19 Apr), Taurus (20 Apr – 20 May), Gemini
							(21 May – 20 Jun), Cancer (21 Jun – 22 Jul), Leo (23 Jul – 22
							Aug), Virgo (23 Aug – 22 Sep), Libra (23 Sep – 22 Oct), Scorpio
							(23 Oct – 21 Nov), and Sagittarius (22 Nov – 21 Dec). Browse the
							reference grid on this page for a quick overview.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>What does it mean to be born on a cusp?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A cusp birth falls within a day or two of when one zodiac sign
							ends and the next begins — for example, 22 July sits near the
							Cancer–Leo boundary. Some astrologers believe cusp births blend
							traits from both neighbouring signs, though mainstream tropical
							astrology assigns a single sign based on which date range your
							birthday falls in. Clockr flags dates near a boundary so you can
							explore both signs if you wish.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>What is my birthstone based on my zodiac sign?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Birthstones are traditionally linked to your birth month rather
							than your zodiac sign directly. January is garnet, February
							amethyst, March aquamarine, April diamond, May emerald, June pearl,
							July ruby, August peridot, September sapphire, October opal,
							November topaz, and December turquoise. Clockr shows your
							birthstone based on the month you were born, alongside your star
							sign.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>What are the four zodiac elements?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The twelve signs are grouped into four elements: Fire (Aries, Leo,
							Sagittarius), Earth (Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn), Air (Gemini,
							Libra, Aquarius), and Water (Cancer, Scorpio, Pisces). In
							astrological tradition, each element is associated with a broad
							style of temperament — Fire with passion and action, Earth with
							practicality, Air with intellect and communication, and Water with
							emotion and intuition.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="zsf-faq-item">
					<summary class="zsf-faq-question"
						>Is astrology scientifically proven?</summary
					>
					<div class="zsf-faq-answer">
						<p>
							No. Controlled scientific studies have not found evidence that
							zodiac signs predict personality, compatibility, or life events
							beyond chance. Astrology remains a cultural and symbolic tradition
							rather than an empirically validated system. Many people enjoy it
							as entertainment or personal reflection — Clockr presents your sign
							in that spirit.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="zsf-related">
			<h3 class="zsf-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="zsf-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="zsf-related-card"
					><span class="zsf-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="zsf-related-card"
					><span class="zsf-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="zsf-related-card"
					><span class="zsf-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
				<a href="/anniversary-calculator" class="zsf-related-card"
					><span class="zsf-related-name">Anniversary Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.zsf-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.zsf-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.zsf-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.zsf-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.zsf-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.zsf-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.zsf-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.zsf-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.zsf-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.zsf-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.zsf-input::placeholder) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	:global(.zsf-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.zsf-results) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-sign-heading) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 48px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin: 0 0 8px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-sign-symbol) {
		font-family: 'Segoe UI Symbol', 'Apple Symbols', sans-serif;
		font-size: 48px;
		line-height: 1;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
	}

	:global(.zsf-sign-name) {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	:global(.zsf-date-range) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin: 0 0 24px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-details) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
		text-align: left;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-detail-row) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-detail-label) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	:global(.zsf-detail-value) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	:global(.zsf-color-list) {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-color-item) {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-color-swatch) {
		width: 14px;
		height: 14px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	:global(.zsf-compat-chips) {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-compat-chip) {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.25);
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 6px 12px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-vibe-card) {
		text-align: left;
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.04);
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 18px 16px;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		background-clip: padding-box;
		box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2),
			0 0 24px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		position: relative;
	}

	:global(.zsf-vibe-card::before) {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		inset: -1px;
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 1px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45), rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.35));
		-webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
		-webkit-mask-composite: xor;
		mask-composite: exclude;
		pointer-events: none;
	}

	:global(.zsf-vibe-text) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 8px 0 0;
	}

	:global(.zsf-cusp-note) {
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.05);
		border-left: 3px solid #ec4899;
		border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		line-height: 1.6;
		text-align: left;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-section) {
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-item) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-item:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-symbol) {
		font-size: 28px;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-name) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
	}

	:global(.zsf-grid-range) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 10px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		line-height: 1.3;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.zsf-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.zsf-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.zsf-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.zsf-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.zsf-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.zsf-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.zsf-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.zsf-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.zsf-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.zsf-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.zsf-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.zsf-faq-item[open] .zsf-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.zsf-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.zsf-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.zsf-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.zsf-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.zsf-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.zsf-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.zsf-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.zsf-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.zsf-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.zsf-sign-heading) {
			font-size: 36px;
		}

		:global(.zsf-grid) {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}

		.zsf-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
